This money has been received for the charitable purpose of alleviating the distresses of the now-indigent inhabitants of the town of Kingston, who by the ravages of the enemy are reduced to poverty and want, Livingston wrote on March 31, 1778. On Wednesday, a local Red Cross chapter began collecting donations for victims of the hurricane.  Abraham Livingston. A New York National Guard C-5A cargo plane also left Tuesday to pick up equipment in Mississippi and take it to Puerto Rico. Kingston Historian Edwin Ford remembered the letter when Hurricane Hugo ravaged the Carolinas last week. 